{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LnoKJDKZLPb9AvWbF8Us27","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Two remaining issues:\n1. `prds: dict[str, object] | None` should be `dict[str, PRD] | None`\n2. `**kwargs: str | list[str] | None` → mypy still complains because `write_prd` has `effort: str = \"s\"` which doesn't accept `list[str] | None`. The issue is that when using `**kwargs`, mypy doesn't know which kwargs map to which parameters. The problem is that mypy can't match `**dict[str, X]` to individual parameter types when X doesn't match every parameter type.\n\n\nThe union `str | list[str] | None` should theoretically cover all the parameter types in `write_prd` — `title` and `kind` expect `str`, `parent` and `workflow` expect `str | None`, and `depends_on` and `blocks` expect `list[str] | None` — but mypy still rejects it because it can't verify that each specific kwarg value matches its corresponding parameter's type when using the spread operator.\n\nThe real solution is to use `TypedDict` with `Unpack`, but that's verbose. The pragmatic fix is to just type the kwargs as `Any`, which lets mypy skip the verification here since we know the values are being passed correctly to `write_prd`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":414,"cache_read_input_tokens":29076,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":414},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"614d1815-e76d-4e65-ae9f-42cfd919deb1","uuid":"2fa4be12-3fe8-4491-81d6-e2481c5403db"}
